import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

img = cv2.imread("1.jpg", 0)
F = np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fft2(img))
M, N = img.shape

D0 = 40
  
u, v = np.meshgrid(np.arange(M), np.arange(N), indexing='ij')
D = np.sqrt((u - M/2)**2 + (v - N/2)**2)

H = np.zeros((M, N))
for i in range(M):
    for j in range(N):
        H[i, j] = np.exp(-D[i, j]**2 / (2 * D0**2))

output = np.abs(np.fft.ifft2(F * H))

plt.subplot(1,2,1); plt.imshow(img,cmap='gray'); plt.title("Original")
plt.subplot(1,2,2); plt.imshow(output,cmap='gray'); plt.title("Gaussian LPF")
plt.show()

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

F = np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fft2(img))

u, v = np.meshgrid(np.arange(M), np.arange(N), indexing='ij')

H = np.zeros((M, N))

import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

img = cv2.imread("1.jpg", 0)
F = np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fft2(img))
M, N = img.shape

D0 = 40
n = 2

u, v = np.meshgrid(np.arange(M), np.arange(N), indexing='ij')
D = np.sqrt((u - M/2)**2 + (v - N/2)**2)

H = np.zeros((M, N))
for i in range(M):
    for j in range(N):
        H[i, j] = 1 / (1 + (D[i, j] / D0)**(2*n))

output = np.abs(np.fft.ifft2(np.fft.ifftshift(F * H)))

plt.subplot(1,2,1); plt.imshow(img,cmap='gray'); plt.title("Original")
plt.subplot(1,2,2); plt.imshow(output,cmap='gray'); plt.title("Butterworth LPF")
plt.show()

import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

img = cv2.imread("1.jpg", 0)
F = np.fft.fftshift(np.fft.fft2(img))
M, N = img.shape

D0 = 40

# Distance matrix
u, v = np.meshgrid(np.arange(M), np.arange(N), indexing='ij')
D = np.sqrt((u - M/2)**2 + (v - N/2)**2)

# ILPF using for-loop
H = np.zeros((M, N))
for i in range(M):
    for j in range(N):
        if D[i, j] <= D0:
            H[i, j] = 1

output = np.abs(np.fft.ifft2(np.fft.ifftshift(F * H)))

plt.subplot(1,2,1); plt.imshow(img,cmap='gray'); plt.title("Original")
plt.subplot(1,2,2); plt.imshow(output,cmap='gray'); plt.title("Ideal LPF")
plt.show()

import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Read binary image
img = cv2.imread("111111.png", 0)

# Manual kernel
kernel = np.array([
    [1,1,1],
    [1,1,1],
    [1,1,1]
], dtype=np.uint8)

M, N = img.shape
kM, kN = kernel.shape
pad = kM // 2

# Pad image
padded = np.pad(img, pad, mode='constant')

erosion = np.zeros_like(img)

# -------- Erosion with 'fits' variable --------
for i in range(M):
    for j in range(N):
        region = padded[i:i+kM, j:j+kN]

        # fits = True if every kernel=1 position matches 255 in region
        fits = np.all(region[kernel == 1] == 255)

        erosion[i, j] = 255 if fits else 0

# Show images
plt.subplot(1,2,1); plt.imshow(img, cmap='gray'); plt.title("Original")
plt.subplot(1,2,2); plt.imshow(erosion, cmap='gray'); plt.title("Erosion")
plt.show()
In [90]:
import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

img = cv2.imread("111111.png", 0)
_, binary = cv2.threshold(img, 127, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY)

kernel = np.array([
    [1,1,1],
    [1,1,1],
    [1,1,1]
], dtype=np.uint8)

M, N = binary.shape
kM, kN = kernel.shape
pad = kM // 2

padded = np.pad(binary, pad, mode='constant')
dilation = np.zeros_like(binary)

# -------- DILATION --------
for i in range(M):
    for j in range(N):
        region = padded[i:i+kM, j:j+kN]
        hit = np.any(region[kernel == 1] == 255)
        dilation[i, j] = 255 if hit else 0

# Show
plt.subplot(1,2,1); plt.imshow(binary, cmap='gray'); plt.title("Binary")
plt.subplot(1,2,2); plt.imshow(dilation, cmap='gray'); plt.title("Dilation")
plt.show()

import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

img = cv2.imread("111111.png", 0)
_, binary = cv2.threshold(img, 127, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY)

kernel = np.array([
    [1,1,1],
    [1,1,1],
    [1,1,1]
], dtype=np.uint8)

M, N = binary.shape
kM, kN = kernel.shape
pad = kM // 2

# -------- EROSION --------
padded = np.pad(binary, pad, mode='constant')
eroded = np.zeros_like(binary)

for i in range(M):
    for j in range(N):
        region = padded[i:i+kM, j:j+kN]
        fits = np.all(region[kernel == 1] == 255)
        eroded[i, j] = 255 if fits else 0

# -------- DILATION on ERODED IMAGE --------
padded2 = np.pad(eroded, pad, mode='constant')
opening = np.zeros_like(binary)

for i in range(M):
    for j in range(N):
        region = padded2[i:i+kM, j:j+kN]
        hit = np.any(region[kernel == 1] == 255)
        opening[i, j] = 255 if hit else 0

# Show
plt.figure(figsize=(12,4))
plt.subplot(1,3,1); plt.imshow(binary, cmap='gray'); plt.title("Binary")
plt.subplot(1,3,2); plt.imshow(eroded, cmap='gray'); plt.title("Erosion Step")
plt.subplot(1,3,3); plt.imshow(opening, cmap='gray'); plt.title("Opening")
plt.show()

import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

img = cv2.imread("111111.png", 0)
_, binary = cv2.threshold(img, 127, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY)

kernel = np.array([
    [1,1,1],
    [1,1,1],
    [1,1,1]
], dtype=np.uint8)

M, N = binary.shape
kM, kN = kernel.shape
pad = kM // 2

# -------- DILATION --------
padded = np.pad(binary, pad, mode='constant')
dilated = np.zeros_like(binary)

for i in range(M):
    for j in range(N):
        region = padded[i:i+kM, j:j+kN]
        hit = np.any(region[kernel == 1] == 255)
        dilated[i, j] = 255 if hit else 0

# -------- EROSION on DILATED IMAGE --------
padded2 = np.pad(dilated, pad, mode='constant')
closing = np.zeros_like(binary)

for i in range(M):
    for j in range(N):
        region = padded2[i:i+kM, j:j+kN]
        fits = np.all(region[kernel == 1] == 255)
        closing[i, j] = 255 if fits else 0

# Show
plt.figure(figsize=(12,4))
plt.subplot(1,3,1); plt.imshow(binary, cmap='gray'); plt.title("Binary")
plt.subplot(1,3,2); plt.imshow(dilated, cmap='gray'); plt.title("Dilation Step")
plt.subplot(1,3,3); plt.imshow(closing, cmap='gray'); plt.title("Closing")
plt.show()

import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Read image
img = cv2.imread("Screenshot 2025-11-22 121426.png", 0)

kernel = np.ones((3,3), np.uint8)

# ---- Stage 1: Erosion (1 line) ----
erosion = cv2.erode(img, kernel, iterations=1)

# ---- Stage 2: Opening (Erosion  Dilation) (1 line) ----
opening = cv2.morphologyEx(img, cv2.MORPH_OPEN, kernel)

# Show results
plt.figure(figsize=(12,4))
plt.subplot(1,3,1); plt.imshow(img, cmap='gray'); plt.title("Original")
plt.subplot(1,3,2); plt.imshow(erosion, cmap='gray'); plt.title("Erosion (Stage 1)")
plt.subplot(1,3,3); plt.imshow(opening, cmap='gray'); plt.title("Opening (Final)")
plt.show()

import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load image
img = cv2.imread("1.jpg", 0).astype(np.float32)

M, N = img.shape
pad = 1
padded = np.pad(img, pad, mode='reflect')
out = np.zeros_like(img)

# Arithmetic Mean Filter
for i in range(M):
    for j in range(N):
        region = padded[i:i+3, j:j+3]
        out[i, j] = np.mean(region)

# Display
plt.subplot(1,2,1); plt.imshow(img, cmap='gray'); plt.title("Input")
plt.subplot(1,2,2); plt.imshow(out, cmap='gray'); plt.title("Arithmetic Mean Output")
plt.show()

import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

img = cv2.imread("1.jpg", 0).astype(np.float32) + 1e-6

M, N = img.shape
pad = 1
padded = np.pad(img, pad, mode='reflect')
out = np.zeros_like(img)

# Geometric Mean
for i in range(M):
    for j in range(N):
        region = padded[i:i+3, j:j+3]
        out[i, j] = np.exp(np.mean(np.log(region)))

plt.subplot(1,2,1); plt.imshow(img, cmap='gray'); plt.title("Input")
plt.subplot(1,2,2); plt.imshow(out, cmap='gray'); plt.title("Geometric Mean Output")
plt.show()
